[{"name":"amendment","pos":"noun","content":"<div class=\"entry\" hclass=\"entry\" sum=\"719\" sk=\"amendment: :0\" hlength=\"9\" id=\"amendment\" htag=\"section\" idm_id=\"000001712\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"amendment_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" id=\"amendment_h_1\" ox5000=\"y\" htag=\"h1\" academic=\"y\" hclass=\"headword\">amendment</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">noun</span><div class=\"symbols\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"symbols\"><a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/wordlists/oxford3000-5000?dataset=english&amp;list=ox5000&amp;level=c1\"><span class=\"ox5ksym_c1\">&nbsp;</span></a></div><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" hclass=\"phons_br\" wd=\"amendment\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/a/ame/amend/amendment__gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/a/ame/amend/amendment__gb_1.ogg\" title=\"amendment pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/əˈmendmənt/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" geo=\"n_am\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"amendment\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/a/ame/amend/amendment__us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/a/ame/amend/amendment__us_1.ogg\" title=\"amendment pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/əˈmendmənt/</span></div></span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"senses_multiple\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" ox5000=\"y\" htag=\"li\" id=\"amendment_sng_1\" cefr=\"c1\" hclass=\"sense\" sensenum=\"1\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><div class=\"symbols\" hclass=\"symbols\" htag=\"div\"><a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/wordlists/oxford3000-5000?dataset=english&amp;list=ox5000&amp;level=c1\"><span class=\"ox5ksym_c1\">&nbsp;</span></a></div></span><span class=\"grammar\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"grammar\">[countable, uncountable]</span> <span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">a small change or improvement that is made to a document or proposed new law; the process of changing a document or proposed new law</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">to <span class=\"cl\">introduce/propose/table an amendment</span> <span class=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"gloss\">(= to suggest it)</span></span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Parliament passed the bill without further amendment.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"> <span class=\"cf\" hclass=\"cf\" htag=\"span\">amendment to something</span> <span class=\"x\">She made several minor amendments to her essay.</span></li></ul><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"amendment_unbox_1\" unbox=\"extra_examples\"><span class=\"box_title\">Extra Examples</span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">In total 217 MPs backed the rebel amendment opposing the government.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">On a free vote, the amendment was carried by 292 votes to 246.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Parliament accepted the amendment and the bill was passed.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">She withdrew her amendment and left the meeting.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The Senate added numerous amendments to the bill.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The committee does not adequately consult others when drafting amendments.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The new clause was accepted without amendment.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The programme is subject to amendment.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">an amendment to the Clean Water Act</span></li></ul></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"snippet\" id=\"amendment_unbox_2\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adjective</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">important</li><li class=\"li\">major</li><li class=\"li\">significant</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">verb + amendment</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">introduce</li><li class=\"li\">make</li><li class=\"li\">draft</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">amendment + verb</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">pass (something)</li><li class=\"li\">ban something</li><li class=\"li\">outlaw something</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">preposition</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">without amendment</li><li class=\"li\">amendment to</li></ul><span class=\"xref_to_full_entry\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/collocations/amendment\" title=\" definition in Collocations\n \">full entry</a></span></span></span></div>          \n</li><li class=\"sense\" hclass=\"sense\" sensenum=\"2\" htag=\"li\" id=\"amendment_sng_2\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><div class=\"variants\" type=\"alt\" hclass=\"variants\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"v-g\"><span class=\"v\">Amendment</span></span></div></span> <span class=\"grammar\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"grammar\">[countable]</span> <span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">a statement of a change to the Constitution of the US</span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The 19th Amendment gave women the right to vote.</span></li></ul> <span class=\"xrefs\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"xrefs\" xt=\"see\"><span class=\"prefix\">see also</span> <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-eighteenth-amendment\" title=\"Eighteenth Amendment definition\"><span class=\"xr-g\" href=\"theeighteenthamendment_e\" bord=\"n\"><span class=\"xh\">Eighteenth Amendment</span></span></a></span><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" source=\"ald9_guide\" unbox=\"cult\" id=\"amendment_unbox_3\"><span class=\"box_title\">Culture</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">In the US the first ten <span class=\"dh\">amendments</span> to the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/constitution#constitution_sng_1\" title=\"Constitution definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Constitution</span></a> are called the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bill-of-rights\" title=\"bill of rights definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">bill of rights</span></a>. Each amendment to the US Constitution needs a two-thirds majority in each House and must be approved by 75% of the states.</span></span></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"extra_examples\" id=\"amendment_unbox_4\"><span class=\"box_title\">Extra Examples</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">He is simply exercising his First-Amendment rights.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">a call to repeal the 22nd amendment to the Constitution</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">They have proposed an amendment to the federal constitution.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">a constitutional amendment allowing same-sex marriage</span></li></ul></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"snippet\" id=\"amendment_unbox_5\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adjective</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">important</li><li class=\"li\">major</li><li class=\"li\">significant</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">verb + amendment</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">introduce</li><li class=\"li\">make</li><li class=\"li\">draft</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">amendment + verb</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">pass (something)</li><li class=\"li\">ban something</li><li class=\"li\">outlaw something</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">preposition</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">without amendment</li><li class=\"li\">amendment to</li></ul><span class=\"xref_to_full_entry\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/collocations/amendment\" title=\" definition in Collocations\n \">full entry</a></span></span></span></div>      </li><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"wordorigin\" id=\"amendment_unbox_6\"><span class=\"box_title\">Word Origin</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">Middle English (in the sense ‘improvement, correction’): from Old French <span class=\"ei\">amendement</span>, from <span class=\"ei\">amender</span>, based on Latin <span class=\"ei\">emendare</span>, from <span class=\"ei\">e-</span> (variant of <span class=\"ei\">ex-</span>) ‘out of’ + <span class=\"ei\">menda</span> ‘a fault’.</span></span></span></div></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/amendment\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">amendment</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/amendment\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">amendment</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/amendment\">amendment</a></div></div>\n","matches":["the Fifth Amendment","the First Amendment noun","the Second Amendment","the Eighteenth Amendment noun","the Fourteenth Amendment noun","the Equal Rights Amendment","Fifth Amendment","Equal Rights Amendment"],"relatives":["the Fifth Amendment","the First Amendment noun","the Second Amendment","the Eighteenth Amendment noun","the Fourteenth Amendment noun","the Equal Rights Amendment","Fifth Amendment","Equal Rights Amendment"],"nearBys":["amenable adjective","amend verb","amendment noun","amends noun","amenity noun"]},[{"name":"the Fifth Amendment","pos":"adjective","content":"<div class=\"entry\" sk=\"fifthamendment: :15\" hlength=\"19\" id=\"the-fifth-amendment\" htag=\"section\" hclass=\"entry\" sum=\"560\" idm_id=\"000021824\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"the_fifth_amendment_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" hclass=\"headword\" id=\"the_fifth_amendment_h_1\" htag=\"h1\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"the_fifth_amendment_st_1\">the</span> Fifth Amendment</h1> <span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" hclass=\"phons_br\" wd=\"the Fifth Amendment\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/f/fif/fifth/fifth_amendment_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/f/fif/fifth/fifth_amendment_1_gb_1.ogg\" title=\"the Fifth Amendment pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌfɪfθ əˈmendmənt/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" geo=\"n_am\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"the Fifth Amendment\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/f/fif/fifth/fifth_amendment_1_us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/f/fif/fifth/fifth_amendment_1_us_1.ogg\" title=\"the Fifth Amendment pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌfɪfθ əˈmendmənt/</span></div></span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"fifthamendment_sng_1\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">one of the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/amendment\" title=\"amendments definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">amendments</span></a> to the American Constitution which is part of the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bill-of-rights\" title=\"Bill of Rights definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Bill of Rights</span></a>. It states that people need not say anything against themselves in a court of law. However, when people 'take the Fifth' or ' <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/plead#plead_sng_4\" title=\"plead definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">plead</span></a> the Fifth' in court, some people believe it is because they are guilty. The Fifth Amendment also protects individuals from <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/double-jeopardy\" title=\"double jeopardy definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">double jeopardy</span></a> and requires <span class=\"ndv\" tofix=\"\" xt=\"andv\" href=\"dueprocessoflaw_d_1\">due process of law</span> and fair payments in cases of <span class=\"ndv\" xt=\"andv\" href=\"eminentdomain_d_1\" tofix=\"\">eminent domain</span>.</span></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-fifth-amendment\">the Fifth Amendment</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["fifth ordinal number","fifth noun","the Fifth Amendment","Fifth Avenue","fifth column noun"]},{"name":"the First Amendment","pos":"noun","content":"<div class=\"entry\" sk=\"firstamendment: :15\" hlength=\"19\" id=\"the-first-amendment\" htag=\"section\" hclass=\"entry\" sum=\"293\" idm_id=\"000022113\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"the_first_amendment_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" htag=\"h1\" id=\"the_first_amendment_h_1\" hclass=\"headword\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"the_first_amendment_st_1\">the</span> First Amendment</h1> <span class=\"pos\" hclass=\"pos\" htag=\"span\">noun</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" hclass=\"phons_br\" wd=\"First Amendment\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/f/fir/first/first_amendment_1_gb_2.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/f/fir/first/first_amendment_1_gb_2.ogg\" title=\"First Amendment pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌfɜːst əˈmendmənt/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"n_am\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"First Amendment\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/f/fir/first/first_amendment_1_us_2.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/f/fir/first/first_amendment_1_us_2.ogg\" title=\"First Amendment pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌfɜːrst əˈmendmənt/</span></div></span><span class=\"grammar\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"grammar\">[singular]</span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" id=\"firstamendment_sng_1\" htag=\"li\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">the statement in the US Constitution that protects freedom of speech and religion and the right to meet in peaceful groups</span></span><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"cult\" source=\"ald9_guide\" id=\"firstamendment_unbox_1\"><span class=\"box_title\">Culture</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">The First Amendment forms part of the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bill-of-rights\" title=\"bill of rights definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">bill of rights</span></a>. It is often used by journalists to protect their sources and by the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-supreme-court\" title=\"Supreme Court definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Supreme Court</span></a> to explain why it cannot limit offensive communications.</span></span></span></div>    \n</li></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/the-first-amendment\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">the First Amendment</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-first-amendment\">the First Amendment</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["first aid noun","first-aider noun","the First Amendment noun","first balcony noun","first base noun"]},{"name":"the Second Amendment","pos":"adjective","content":"<div class=\"entry\" htag=\"section\" id=\"the-second-amendment\" hlength=\"20\" sk=\"secondamendment: :15\" sum=\"731\" hclass=\"entry\" idm_id=\"000052901\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"the_second_amendment_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" hclass=\"headword\" id=\"the_second_amendment_h_1\" htag=\"h1\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"the_second_amendment_st_1\">the</span> Second Amendment</h1> <span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" wd=\"the Second Amendment\" hclass=\"phons_br\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/s/sec/secon/second_amendment_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/s/sec/secon/second_amendment_1_gb_1.ogg\" title=\"the Second Amendment pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌsekənd əˈmendmənt/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"the Second Amendment\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"n_am\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/s/sec/secon/second_amendment_1_us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/s/sec/secon/second_amendment_1_us_1.ogg\" title=\"the Second Amendment pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌsekənd əˈmendmənt/</span></div></span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" id=\"secondamendment_sng_1\" htag=\"li\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">an <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/amendment\" title=\"amendment definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">amendment</span></a> <span class=\"gloss\" hclass=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\">(= change)</span> to the American Constitution, part of the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bill-of-rights\" title=\"Bill of Rights definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Bill of Rights</span></a>, passed in 1791. The Second Amendment gives people the right to bear arms <span class=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"gloss\">(= to own and carry weapons)</span>. This has become an issue because of a number of recent <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/tragic#tragic_sng_1\" title=\"tragic definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">tragic</span></a> events when one armed person has shot a number of people. There is now much <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/disagreement#disagreement_sng_1\" title=\"disagreement definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">disagreement</span></a> over what this Amendment actually means. Some people believe it only applies to the military and others that it applies to all citizens. It states: ‘A well regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free State, the right of people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be infringed.’</span></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-second-amendment\">the Second Amendment</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["second1 verb","second2 verb","the Second Amendment","secondarily adverb","secondary adjective"]},{"name":"the Eighteenth Amendment","pos":"noun","content":"<div class=\"entry\" htag=\"section\" hlength=\"24\" id=\"the-eighteenth-amendment\" sk=\"eighteenthamendment: :15\" sum=\"377\" hclass=\"entry\" idm_id=\"000018985\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"eighteenthamendment_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" htag=\"h1\" id=\"eighteenthamendment_h_1\" random=\"y\" hclass=\"headword\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"eighteenthamendment_st_1\">the</span> Eighteenth Amendment</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">noun</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\" wd=\"the Eighteenth Amendment\" hclass=\"phons_br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/t/the/the_e/the_eighteenth_amendment_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/t/the/the_e/the_eighteenth_amendment_1_gb_1.ogg\" title=\"the Eighteenth Amendment pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ði ˌeɪtiːn